          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-07-16 19:46:02" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to be in existence, having life, not dead</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be alive</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to live</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some figurative expressions ζάω[a] and ζωή may involve serious complications in reference. For example, in {S:04300605100038} the expression ἐγώ εἰμι ὁ ἄρτος ὁ ζῶν ‘I am the living bread’ may be understood in some languages as bread which has some living objects in it, namely, bread which is being eaten by worms or weevils. It may therefore be necessary to say ‘I am that bread which gives life.’{N:001}|In a number of languages there is no noun-like word for ‘life.’ It may therefore be necessary to change all passages which speak of ‘life’ into a corresponding expression using a verb-like form meaning ‘to live.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
