          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-07-16 19:46:02" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to come back to life after having once died</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to come back to life</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to live again</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to be resurrected</Gloss>
                <Gloss>resurrection</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages there is a difficulty involved in formulating some expression for ‘resurrection’ or ‘living again,’ since such a phrase may refer to what is technically known as metempsychosis, that is to say, the rebirth of the soul in another existence, a belief which is widely held in a number of areas of south Asia. This problem may be avoided in some languages by speaking of ‘his body will live again’ or ‘his body will come back to life’ or ‘he will be the same person when he lives again.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
