              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to conduct oneself, with the particular manner specified by the context</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to live</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to conduct oneself</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to behave</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:05500301200014} ζάω does not refer to physiological existence, but rather to the manner in which a person behaves or conducts himself in relationship to other persons and to God.</Comments>
